<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-09T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/38: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-09T11:00:00-04:00">September 9, 1937—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>37. My 36, September 8, 10 a.m. Government has situation well controlled.
                            Business going on normally this morning although there are still some
                            armed troops patrolling. Minister for Foreign Affairs states that the
                            country districts are quiet.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>